The paper focuses on developing a dynamic spiking neural network, which is a subfield of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model on image recognition datasets, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the flexibility and ability to handle complex nonlinear structures, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new type of neural network, which can be considered as a control system (cs.SY).
